8d2c8c88-63ae-57b3-883b-634eb7dfa059,tg:rubgr:1907,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

[recto] In favour: Difference of eyes, the left one round. Technique to be studied. The surface coarser than Munich woman, but hair looks good, cf. Blind Man, pl. 151. Does Bruegel ever paint such a "(*) mouth line" technique. Isn't the form too simple compared with e.g. pl. 137. (*) cf. [onleesbaar] in pl.130. Colour of background like in the Munich Head. For the mouth line, cf. King left border in London Adoration & painter in the Albertina drawing, T. 118.; [verso]The background more brown grey than in repr. A system of pink lines up cheek.The shadows in cross hatchings very fine like with feather in brown ink.[scan]

<part_of.title>Autumn Exhibition of Flemish, Dutch and Italian Old Masters: Catalogue 3/6, November 2nd to 30th 1959, London: Leonard Koetser, 1959; s.v. Pieter Brueghel the Elder, 17. Head of a Peasant;[afmetingen doorstreept en vervangen door]: 25 x 18 cm. [notitie bij 'Literature']: Brueghel dit le Paysan 282. Une belle tête de paysan. Peinte sur bois, hauteur 9 pouces, sur autant de largeur; [Jacob von Falke] Katalog der fürstlich Liechtensteinischen Bilder-Galerie im Gartenpalais der Rossau zu Wien, Wien 1873, p. 128, N° 1110 [notitie] Peter Brueghel d.Ält. Kopf eines bäuerischen Mannes mit kurzem Bart und schmarzer Kappe, H. 0.25 -0.18.</part_of.title>
